		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Madison WI Misty Mountain 3/12/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.82)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8714'>Xanthix "Xanthix" Xanthix</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8714&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 13, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Tournament Report<br>
3/12/2002<br>
Misty Mountain Game Shop Tuesday Night Tournament<br>
<br>
I find out that Misty Mountain (In Madison - great store!) runs LOTR tournaments on Tuesdays, and since I can&#39;t do anything on the weekends, I think this is the best thing since sliced bread. There aren&#39;t enough present to make it official (only 6), so we do an informal tourney for some local foils.<br>
<br>
I bring my decks, and use my Poor Man&#39;s Swarm deck (see my page for the decklist). The free peoples take it slow, with pipes for healing, and the shadow side is a rareless Moria swarm. I won&#39;t win any awards for deck design but I figure why not, I&#39;m here to play.<br>
<br>
Game 1: Steve (shop owner)<br>
<br>
Steve is using a borrowed deck and isn&#39;t even sure what&#39;s in it - he&#39;s just playing so we have an even number of people (thanks Steve!). He bids 5 and keeps saying he doesn&#39;t play LOTR enough, so I was hoping this might be an easy game. Those hopes are dashed when, at site 1, he has Aragorn, his sword and bow, Legolas Greenleaf, his bow, and Sam to remove 3 burdens. On my first turn I think I played a hobbit sword. Hmm, maybe I should look into buying some cards... Anyway, he moves 2 sites a turn, and I play Goblins as fast as I can, but I don&#39;t draw any recursion and it seems like I can only play a big swarm after he heals all his archers. My fellowship suffers from the attention of the Watching Eye and some Orc Bowmen, but hey, I start 4 hobbits for a reason - that&#39;s 16 vitality to soak up wounds! Anyway, we get to the site 7 where there&#39;s no archery, and I have a chance, but by then he has Gimli and his axe too and I can&#39;t play enough Goblins and he makes it to site 9.<br>
<br>
Result: Full Loss (1 point)<br>
<br>
Game 2: Chris<br>
<br>
Chris seems like a great guy, he&#39;s really friendly. Didn&#39;t know what to expect from his deck but he started foil Arwen and Greeny... hmmm not good for our side. :) However, my deck decides to make up for the last game, and stacks itself in my favor. I start Boromir and Merry this time, and by turn 2 or so I get all three pipes out. Heal up, remove twilight. I&#39;m also able to play They Are Coming and Goblin Armory in preparation. Meanwhile, Chris&#39;s deck decides to be uncooperative, and I move only once per turn to try to prevent him from drawing more (at one point he uses Hates a full-vitality Sam just to get it out of his hand). He plays some elf allies and some Sauron trackers, which I&#39;m able to survive fine. Then at site 4, my deck explodes with 5 goblins, all armed. Before I play the last weapon, he&#39;s recorded it as a loss on his sheet. ^_^; Chris is a great guy though and we talk afterwards. Sorry you&#39;re having a losing streak Chris!<br>
<br>
Result: Full Win (4 points now)<br>
<br>
Game 3: Tony<br>
<br>
Tony was the informal tournament director tonight. His deck turns out to be Sauron too, with a whole lotta elves. He starts Arwen and someone else, and soon has Greenleaf out, backing up Aragorn and his sword and bow, both with +1 vitality. Not to mention Galadriel, Celeborn, and the ally that shoots orcs. Doh! My draws are significantly less exciting, and he is so good at shooting orcs that he only has to assign for a skirmish like 3 times. He has my poor Goblins on the run so bad that even Galadriel comes to beat them up (via Swanship). The annoying thing is that every fellowship phase, he&#39;s able to heal up completely. I might have had a chance at my site 7 (no archery) but he draws a Map and plays a different one. While all this is going on, he&#39;s playing Under the Watching Eye and Orc Bowmen x3. Ouch ouch ouch! All my guys end up exhausted, and he even kills Boromir with some evil sneaky Sauron event (mental note: read spoiler list before next time). Frodo decides to give the ring to the nice strength 200 Band of the Eye at site 6 after Pippin dies too. Overall I was impressed with how well Tony played this game.<br>
<br>
Result: Full Loss (5 points now)<br>
<br>
<br>
We were going to have another round, but people had to leave (and I think I was coming down with something) so we totaled scores then. I didn&#39;t win a foil but I was able to trade for a Power and Terror and Whip of Many Thongs. Overall, it was really fun. It was a good first tournament for me, and I was glad to meet everyone I got to play against. Also I got to see the local metagame (stoopid Sauron) and got some ideas for how to make my deck better (Step 1: throw out current deck. Step 2...). If I say what the moral of the story was, I&#39;d say &quot;be prepared for massive aimed archery.&quot;<br>
<br>
Thanks to everyone to participated, and Misty Mountain for easily being the best gaming store I&#39;ve ever been to as far as space for gaming. You should see this place - a huge gaming room with tables, side rooms with couches for RPGs and miniatures tables with scenery, and a computer LAN room. I think I&#39;ll be coming back for more tourneys!<br>
<br>
Oh and by the way, for anyone in the area. On April 2nd, they&#39;ll be running a LOTR tournament, the prize of which will be a foil rare Balrog: Flame of Udun. You know you want it. :) See tournaments.decipher.com for details.<br>
<br>
